      </div>
      <h3 class='article'>
        <a name="wzhou"></a>
        Western Zhou Dynasty
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=17055' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Xī Zhōu', 'Western Zhou')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">西周</a>
      </h3>
      <p>
        The Zhou clan overthrew Emperor Wuwang of the Shang Dynasty in 1,046 BCE.
        The <span class='bookTitle'>zhi</span> <a href='/word_detail.php?id=25727' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '觶 zhì', 'zhi / a wine vessel')" 
        onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>觯</a>, a kind of wine cup, below belonged to an official named Shan, who was rewarded 
        with this prize for his part in a campaign to thwart a Zhou come back.
        The inscription inside the <span class='bookTitle'>zhi</span> provides valuable archaeological confirmation of ancient
        written records and that the commander of this particular battle was the 
        <span class='bookTitle'>Duke of Zhou</span> <a href='/word_detail.php?id=26406' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Zhōu Gōng Dàn', 'Duke of Zhou')" 
        onmouseout="hideToolTip()">周公旦</a>.
      </p>
      <div class="picture">
        <a href='illustrations_use.php?mediumResolution=bronze_xiaochen_cup_wzhou400.jpg'><img class='use' src='images/bronze_xiaochen_cup_wzhou400.jpg' alt='zhi / a wine vessel' title='zhi / a wine vessel'/></a>
        <div>
          <div class='picture_header'><a href='/word_detail.php?id=762' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'xiǎo', 'small / young')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">小</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=6967' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'chén', 'statesman / vassal / courtier / minister / official')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">臣</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=4620' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '單 Shàn', 'Shan')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">单</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=25727' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '觶 zhì', 'zhi / a wine vessel')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">觯</a></div>
          <a href='/word_detail.php?id=17055' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Xī Zhōu', 'Western Zhou')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">西周</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=22365' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Chéng Wáng', 'King Cheng of Zhou')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">成王</a>（<a href='/word_detail.php?id=22414' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Gōng​yuán​ Qián', 'Before the Common Era (BCE)')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">公元前</a>11<a href='/word_detail.php?id=743' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '世紀 shì​jì​', 'century')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">世纪</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=23570' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '上半葉 shàngbànyè', 'the first half')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">上半叶</a>） <a href='/word_detail.php?id=1559' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Shànghǎi', 'Shanghai')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">上海</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=3974' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '博物館 bówù​guǎn', 'Museum')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">博物馆</a>
          <div class='picture_header'>Zhi (wine vessel) for Official Shan</div>
          King Chen Reign, Western Zhou (early 11th century BCE), Shanghai Museum
        </div>
      </div>
      <p>
        Bronze artifacts continued to be central to customs and ceremonies in the Zhou.
        Many of these customs and ceremonies were recorded in 
        <span class='bookTitle'>The Book of Rites</span> <a href='/word_detail.php?id=23741' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '禮記 Lǐ Jì', 'Classic of Rites')" 
        onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>礼记</a>, thought to have originally been compiled by Confucius himself.
        However, it is believed that the version that exists today was reworked in the Han.
        Two other classics describing ceremonies in this period are <span class='bookTitle'>The Rites of Zhou</span> <a href='/word_detail.php?id=25254' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '周禮 Zhōu Lǐ', 'the Rites of Zhou')" 
        onmouseout="hideToolTip()">周礼</a> and <span class='bookTitle'>Yili</span> or
        <span class='bookTitle'>Book of Etiquette and Ceremonial</span> <a href='/word_detail.php?id=26444' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '儀禮 Yí Lǐ', 'Yili / Book of Etiquette and Ceremonial')" 
        onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>仪礼</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        The Western Zhou period ended in 771 BCE when some members of the ethnic tribe Quan Rong captured the Zhou capital and
        killed Emperor Youwang.
        The workmanship improved greatly in the Western Zhou resulting in some very high quality artifacts, even by modern 
        standards.
      </p>
      <a name="bird"></a>
      <div class="picture">
        <a href='illustrations_use.php?mediumResolution=niaowen400.jpg'><img class='use' src='images/niaowen400.jpg' alt='Bronze Ware Pou' title='Bronze Ware Pou'/></a>
        <div>
          <div class='picture_header'><a href='/word_detail.php?id=3648' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'jiǎ', 'armour')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">甲</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=24654' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'guǐ', 'a square basket of bamboo')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">簋</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=273' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'de', 'possessive particle')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">的</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=25276' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '鳳鳥紋 fèng niǎo wén', 'bird designs')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">凤鸟纹</a></div>
          <a href='/word_detail.php?id=17055' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Xī Zhōu', 'Western Zhou')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">西周</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=13726' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'zǎoqī', 'early period / early phase / early stage')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">早期</a>（<a href='/word_detail.php?id=22414' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Gōng​yuán​ Qián', 'Before the Common Era (BCE)')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">公元前</a>11<a href='/word_detail.php?id=743' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '世紀 shì​jì​', 'century')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">世纪</a>） <a href='/word_detail.php?id=1559' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Shànghǎi', 'Shanghai')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">上海</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=3974' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '博物館 bówù​guǎn', 'Museum')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">博物馆</a>
          <div class='picture_header'>Bird Patterns on a Jia Gui (Food Vessel)</div>
          Early Western Zhou Dynasty (11th century BCE), Shanghai Museum
        </div>
      </div>
      <p>
        The use of bronze ware artifacts in religious ceremonies of the Shang continued in the Zhou Dynasty.
        In addition to the vessels of the Shang, bronze musical instruments used in ceremonies have also been found.
        In the middle period, marked by the reigns of Emperor Muwang (976&mdash;922 BCE) and Emperor Yiwang (885&mdash;877BCE)
        artifact types and decorations changed.
        Wine and food vessels became less common and utensils and musical chimes became more dominant.
        Ribbon and abstract geometric patterns replaced the mythical taotie animal of the Shang Dynasty.
        The <span class='bookTitle'>kuilong</span> dragon pattern became popular. 
      </p>
      <a name="animal_mask"></a>
      <div class="picture">
        <a href='illustrations_use.php?mediumResolution=shoumianwen_you_400.jpg'><img class='use' src='images/shoumianwen_you_400.jpg' alt='a wine container' title='a wine container'/></a>
        <a href='illustrations_use.php?mediumResolution=shoumianwen_you_detail400.jpg'><img class='use' src='images/shoumianwen_you_detail400.jpg' alt='a wine container' title='a wine container'/></a>
        <div>
          <div class='picture_header'><a href='/word_detail.php?id=25275' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '獸面紋 shòu miàn wén', 'animal mask design')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">兽面纹</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=25413' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'yǒu', 'a wine container')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">卣</a></div>
          <a href='/word_detail.php?id=17055' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Xī Zhōu', 'Western Zhou')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">西周</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=13726' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'zǎoqī', 'early period / early phase / early stage')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">早期</a>（<a href='/word_detail.php?id=22414' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Gōng​yuán​ Qián', 'Before the Common Era (BCE)')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">公元前</a>11<a href='/word_detail.php?id=743' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '世紀 shì​jì​', 'century')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">世纪</a>） <a href='/word_detail.php?id=1559' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Shànghǎi', 'Shanghai')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">上海</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=3974' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '博物館 bówù​guǎn', 'Museum')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">博物馆</a>
          <div class='picture_header'>You (a Wine Vessel) with Animal Mask Designs</div>
          Early Western Zhou Dynasty (11th century BCE), Shanghai Museum
        </div>
      </div>
      <p>
        The <span class='bookTitle'>zun</span>, shown below, is a large wine vessel.
        It appeared in the Shang and continued to be used until the Western Zhou.
        The neck and bellie of the <span class='bookTitle'>zun</span> is decorated with 
        <span class='bookTitle'>taotie</span> designs.
        The corners of the shoulder are decorated with elephant heads with upturned trunks and tusks.
        The background is covered with fine lightening patterns.
        There is an inscription in this artifact indicating that it was made as a vessel for a sacrificial ceremony for
        Gui Gu.
      </p>
      <div class="picture">
        <a href='illustrations_use.php?mediumResolution=zun_wzhou400.jpg'><img class='use' src='images/zun_wzhou400.jpg' alt='ancient wine vessel' title='ancient wine vessel'/></a>
        <div>
          <div class='picture_header'><a href='/word_detail.php?id=3382' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'fāng', 'square / quadrilateral / direction / one side')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">方</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=6609' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'zū​n', 'to honor / to respect')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">尊</a></div>
          <a href='/word_detail.php?id=17055' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Xī Zhōu', 'Western Zhou')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">西周</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=13726' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'zǎoqī', 'early period / early phase / early stage')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">早期</a>（<a href='/word_detail.php?id=22414' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Gōng​yuán​ Qián', 'Before the Common Era (BCE)')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">公元前</a>11<a href='/word_detail.php?id=743' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '世紀 shì​jì​', 'century')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">世纪</a>） <a href='/word_detail.php?id=1559' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Shànghǎi', 'Shanghai')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">上海</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=3974' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '博物館 bówù​guǎn', 'Museum')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">博物馆</a>
          <div class='picture_header'>Square Zun (a Wine Vessel)</div>
          Early Western Zhou Dynasty (11th century BCE), Shanghai Museum
        </div>
      </div>
      <p>
        There are many idioms associated with <span class='bookTitle'>ding</span>.
        For example, <a href='/word_detail.php?id=26079' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'yī yán jiǔ dǐng', 'words of enormous weight')" 
        onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>一言九鼎</a> “words of enormous weight”, literally one word worth nine sacred ding, 
        the nine ding symbolizing the rule of China; and <a href='/word_detail.php?id=26080' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'dà míng dǐng dǐng', 'a grand reputation / renown / fame')" 
        onmouseout="hideToolTip()">大名鼎鼎</a> “renown.”
      </p>
      <div class="picture">
        <a href='illustrations_use.php?mediumResolution=ding_wzhou400.jpg'><img class='use' src='images/ding_wzhou400.jpg' alt='large, three-legged bronze caldron' title='large, three-legged bronze caldron'/></a>
        <div>
          <div class='picture_header'><a href='/word_detail.php?id=3534' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'jiāo', 'to deliver / to turn over / to make friends / to intersect / to pay')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">交</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=7097' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'dǐng', 'large, three-legged bronze caldron')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">鼎</a></div>
          <a href='/word_detail.php?id=17055' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Xī Zhōu', 'Western Zhou')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">西周</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=13726' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'zǎoqī', 'early period / early phase / early stage')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">早期</a>（<a href='/word_detail.php?id=22414' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Gōng​yuán​ Qián', 'Before the Common Era (BCE)')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">公元前</a>11<a href='/word_detail.php?id=743' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '世紀 shì​jì​', 'century')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">世纪</a>） <a href='/word_detail.php?id=1559' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Shànghǎi', 'Shanghai')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">上海</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=3974' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '博物館 bówù​guǎn', 'Museum')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">博物馆</a>
          <div class='picture_header'>Jiao Ding (a Food Vessel)</div>
          Early Western Zhou Dynasty (11th century BCE), Shanghai Museum
        </div>
      </div>
      <p>
        The <span class='bookTitle'>jue</span>, shown below, is a three legged vessel for drinking wine.
        Bronze <span class='bookTitle'>jue</span> evolved from pottery <span class='bookTitle'>jue</span> in the Xia Dynasty.
      </p>
      <div class="picture">
        <a href='illustrations_use.php?mediumResolution=xijue_wzhou400.jpg'><img class='use' src='images/xijue_wzhou400.jpg' alt='an ancient three legged wine vessel' title='an ancient three legged wine vessel'/></a>
        <div>
          <div class='picture_header'><a href='/word_detail.php?id=25426' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'jué', 'an ancient three legged wine vessel')" 
          onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>角</a></div>
          <a href='/word_detail.php?id=17055' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Xī Zhōu', 'Western Zhou')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">西周</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=13726' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'zǎoqī', 'early period / early phase / early stage')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">早期</a>（<a href='/word_detail.php?id=22414' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Gōng​yuán​ Qián', 'Before the Common Era (BCE)')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">公元前</a>11<a href='/word_detail.php?id=743' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '世紀 shì​jì​', 'century')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">世纪</a>） <a href='/word_detail.php?id=1559' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Shànghǎi', 'Shanghai')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">上海</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=3974' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '博物館 bówù​guǎn', 'Museum')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">博物馆</a>
          <div class='picture_header'>Jue (a Wine Vessel)</div>
          Early Western Zhou Dynasty (11th century BCE), Shanghai Museum
        </div>
      </div>
      <p>
        The historic text <span class='bookTitle'>Rites of Zhou</span> mentions sacrificial rites with six 
        <span class='bookTitle'>zun</span> and six <span class='bookTitle'>yi</span>.
        An <span class='bookTitle'>yi</span> is shown below. 
      </p>
      <div class="picture">
        <a href='illustrations_use.php?mediumResolution=fangyi_wzhou400.jpg'><img class='use' src='images/fangyi_wzhou400.jpg' alt='yi / an ancient wine vessel / an ancient sacrificial vessel' title='yi / an ancient wine vessel / an ancient sacrificial vessel'/></a>
        <div>
          <div class='picture_header'><a href='/word_detail.php?id=3721' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '師 shī', 'teacher / master / expert')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">师</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=17174' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'jù​​​', 'to be swift')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">遽</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=3382' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'fāng', 'square / quadrilateral / direction / one side')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">方</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=25422' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '彞 yí', 'yi / an ancient wine vessel / an ancient sacrificial vessel')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">彝</a></div>
          <a href='/word_detail.php?id=17055' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Xī Zhōu', 'Western Zhou')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">西周</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=6650' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'gōng', 'respectful')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">恭</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=3235' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Wáng', 'Wang')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">王</a>（<a href='/word_detail.php?id=22414' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Gōng​yuán​ Qián', 'Before the Common Era (BCE)')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">公元前</a>10<a href='/word_detail.php?id=743' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '世紀 shì​jì​', 'century')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">世纪</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=20687' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '中葉 zhōng​yè​', 'mid- / middle period')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">中叶</a>） <a href='/word_detail.php?id=1559' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Shànghǎi', 'Shanghai')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">上海</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=3974' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '博物館 bówù​guǎn', 'Museum')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">博物馆</a>
          <div class='picture_header'>Square Yi (a Wine Vessel) belonging to Shi Ju</div>
          King Gong Reign, Western Zhou Dynasty (mid tenth century BCE), Shanghai Museum
        </div>
      </div>
      <p>
        The <span class='bookTitle'>gui</span> appeared in the Shang dynasty and is a food vessel for holding broomcorn millet and 
        other food. 
        In the Western Zhou the <span class='bookTitle'>gui</span> started to be used in even numbers with the ding in odd numbers.
        For example, the emperor would use nine <span class='bookTitle'>ding</span> and eight <span class='bookTitle'>gui</span> 
        and high level nobles would use seven <span class='bookTitle'>ding</span> with six <span class='bookTitle'>gui</span>.
      </p>
      <div class="picture">
        <a href='illustrations_use.php?mediumResolution=shihuangui400.jpg'><img class='use' src='images/shihuangui400.jpg' alt='yi / a water vessel' title='Gui / a food vessel'/></a>
        <div>
          <div class='picture_header'><a href='/word_detail.php?id=3721' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '師 shī', 'teacher / master / expert')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">师</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=21253' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'huán​', 'a large domain')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">寰</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=24654' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'guǐ', 'a square basket of bamboo')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">簋</a></div>
          <a href='/word_detail.php?id=17055' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Xī Zhōu', 'Western Zhou')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">西周</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=22375' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Xuān Wáng', 'King Xuan of Zhou')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">宣王</a>（<a href='/word_detail.php?id=22414' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Gōng​yuán​ Qián', 'Before the Common Era (BCE)')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">公元前</a>827〜<a href='/word_detail.php?id=681' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'qián', 'in front of / before')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">前</a>782） <a href='/word_detail.php?id=1559' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Shànghǎi', 'Shanghai')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">上海</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=3974' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, '博物館 bówù​guǎn', 'Museum')" 
          onmouseout="hideToolTip()">博物馆</a>
          <div class='picture_header'>Shi Huan Gui (a food vessel)</div>
          King Huan Reign, Western Zhou Dynasty (827 &mdash; 782 BCE), Shanghai Museum
        </div>
      </div>
      <p>
        After ceremonial vessels, weapons made up the next greatest proportion of bronze ware.
        For example, in the Shang concubine <span class='bookTitle'>Fu Hao's</span> tomb, about 30 percent of the bronze
        artifacts were weapons.
        After the end of the Warring States Period, Emperor Qin Shi Huang, confiscated all bronze weapons. 
        Some of the bronze weapons, such as the battle ax below, were primarily for ceremonial use.
      </p>
      <div class="picture">
        <a href='illustrations_use.php?mediumResolution=yue_wzhou400.jpg'><img class='use' src='images/yue_wzhou400.jpg' alt='a battle ax' title='a battle ax'/></a>
